# HTML/CSS flow chart (when SVG is overkill)

<p><strong>Use HTML flow when</strong>: small (≤4 nodes), single direction, no precise layout needed.</p>

<div class="flow-chart">
  <div class="flow-row">
    <div class="flow-node long-term"><span class="node-label">Input</span></div>
    <div class="flow-arrow right"></div>
    <div class="flow-node data"><span class="node-label">Process</span></div>
    <div class="flow-arrow right"></div>
    <div class="flow-node output"><span class="node-label">Output</span></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p><strong>Use SVG when</strong>: 5+ nodes, branching, color-coded categories, anything that needs to look polished.</p>

